Understate: The claim understates the fact that Taco Bell itself and its parent company did not donate any money to Roy Moore's Senate campaign.
Lack enough support: The claim lacks enough support to prove that Taco Bell or its owner is the main financier of Roy Moore's campaign.
Problematic assumption: The claim assumes that because a Florida-based owner of Taco Bell franchises donated to Moore's campaign, Taco Bell itself is the main financier.
Exist alternative explanation: There is an alternative explanation that Taco Bell franchises are among the ventures of businessman Peter Nicholas, who is one of Moore's donors.
Exaggerate: The claim exaggerates the connection between Taco Bell and Roy Moore's campaign by stating that Taco Bell is a major supporter of Moore, whereas it is only a donation from one of its franchise owners.
Contradict fact: The claim contradicts the fact that Taco Bell and its parent company did not donate to Moore's campaign.
